  'help.tryDifferentSearch': 'Try a different search term.',
  'help.quickStartStep1Title': '1. Import Your Screenplay',
  'help.quickStartStep1Desc': 'Start by uploading your screenplay in PDF, FDX (Final Draft), or plain text format. SceneMachine will automatically parse scenes, characters, and dialogue.',
  'help.quickStartStep2Title': '2. Design Your Characters',
  'help.quickStartStep2Desc': 'Use the Character Lab to define visual appearances for each character. Add reference images, describe their look, and set consistent attributes.',
  'help.quickStartStep3Title': '3. Plan Your Scenes',
  'help.quickStartStep3Desc': 'Review each scene and plan your shots. Choose shot types, camera angles, and composition. SceneMachine suggests shots based on the screenplay.',
  'help.quickStartStep4Title': '4. Generate Videos',
  'help.quickStartStep4Desc': 'Queue your shots for generation. Watch as AI creates video clips based on your screenplay and visual specifications.',
  'help.quickStartStep5Title': '5. Review & Refine',
  'help.quickStartStep5Desc': 'Preview generated shots, provide feedback, and regenerate any that need improvement. Approve shots that meet your vision.',
  'help.quickStartStep6Title': '6. Export Your Movie',
  'help.quickStartStep6Desc': 'Assemble approved shots into scenes and export your final movie in various formats and quality levels.',
  'help.featureScreenplayParsingTitle': 'Screenplay Parsing',
  'help.featureScreenplayParsingDesc': 'SceneMachine supports multiple screenplay formats including Final Draft (.fdx), PDF, and plain text. The parser identifies scene headings, action lines, character names, dialogue, and parentheticals.',
  'help.featureScreenplayParsingTip1': 'Use standard screenplay formatting for best results',
  'help.featureScreenplayParsingTip2': 'Scene headings should follow INT/EXT format',
  'help.featureScreenplayParsingTip3': 'Character names should be in CAPS',
  'help.featureCharacterLabTitle': 'Character Lab',
  'help.featureCharacterLabDesc': 'The Character Lab allows you to define consistent visual appearances for your characters. Upload reference images, describe physical attributes, and set visual style guides.',
  'help.featureCharacterLabTip1': 'Add multiple reference images for better consistency',
  'help.featureCharacterLabTip2': 'Be specific about age, build, clothing style',
  'help.featureCharacterLabTip3': 'Use the visual style field for artistic direction',
  'help.featureShotPlanningTitle': 'Shot Planning',
  'help.featureShotPlanningDesc': 'Plan your shots with precision using the Scene Planning tools. Choose shot types, camera movements, and composition. Add visual notes and references.',
  'help.featureShotPlanningTip1': 'Use the AI suggestions as a starting point',
  'help.featureShotPlanningTip2': 'Match shot types to the emotional content',
  'help.featureShotPlanningTip3': 'Consider pacing when setting shot durations',
  'help.featureVideoGenerationTitle': 'Video Generation',
  'help.featureVideoGenerationDesc': 'Queue shots for AI video generation. Monitor progress in real-time and manage your generation queue with priority controls.',
  'help.featureVideoGenerationTip1': 'Start with a few test shots to calibrate',
  'help.featureVideoGenerationTip2': 'Use the prompt preview to verify descriptions',
  'help.featureVideoGenerationTip3': 'Higher priority items are processed first',
  'help.featureTimelineEditorTitle': 'Timeline Editor',
  'help.featureTimelineEditorDesc': 'Arrange and fine-tune your shots in the interactive timeline. Adjust durations, reorder clips, and preview the assembled sequence.',
  'help.featureTimelineEditorTip1': 'Use keyboard shortcuts for faster editing',
  'help.featureTimelineEditorTip2': 'Lock clips to prevent accidental changes',
  'help.featureTimelineEditorTip3': 'Preview the sequence before exporting',
  'help.featureExportOptionsTitle': 'Export Options',
  'help.featureExportOptionsDesc': 'Export your final movie in various formats and quality levels. Choose from MP4 (H.264/H.265), ProRes, WebM, and more.',
  'help.featureExportOptionsTip1': 'Use Draft quality for quick previews',
  'help.featureExportOptionsTip2': 'Master quality for final delivery',
  'help.featureExportOptionsTip3': 'H.264 for widest compatibility',
  'help.tipsLabel': 'Tips:',
  'help.faqFormatsQuestion': 'What screenplay formats are supported?',
  'help.faqFormatsAnswer': 'SceneMachine supports Final Draft (.fdx), PDF, Fountain (.fountain), and plain text formats. For best results, use properly formatted screenplays following industry standards.',
  'help.faqGenTimeQuestion': 'How long does video generation take?',
  'help.faqGenTimeAnswer': 'Generation time varies based on the provider, video length, and queue size. Typically, a 3-5 second clip takes 30-60 seconds to generate. You can monitor progress in real-time from the Generation page.',
  'help.faqApiKeysQuestion': 'Can I use my own API keys?',
  'help.faqApiKeysAnswer': 'Yes! Go to Settings > API Keys to configure your own API keys for various providers including Anthropic, OpenAI, Replicate, Fal.ai, RunwayML, and ElevenLabs.',
  'help.faqConsistencyQuestion': 'How do I ensure character consistency?',
  'help.faqConsistencyAnswer': 'Use the Character Lab to define detailed visual descriptions and reference images for each character. The AI will use these references to maintain consistency across shots.',
  'help.faqResolutionsQuestion': 'What video resolutions are available?',
  'help.faqResolutionsAnswer': 'SceneMachine supports 720p, 1080p, 1440p, and 4K resolutions. Higher resolutions may take longer to generate and consume more API credits.',
  'help.faqRegenerateQuestion': 'Can I regenerate a specific shot?',
  'help.faqRegenerateAnswer': 'Yes! You can regenerate any shot from the Scene Planning or Generation pages. Use the feedback feature to provide guidance for the regeneration.',
  'help.faqExportQuestion': 'How do I export my final movie?',
  'help.faqExportAnswer': 'Navigate to the Export page from your project. Choose your preferred format, quality level, and resolution. The export process will assemble all approved shots into a single video file.',
  'help.faqDataSecurityQuestion': 'Is my data stored securely?',
  'help.faqDataSecurityAnswer': 'All project data is stored locally on your machine by default. API keys are encrypted in your system keychain. We recommend regular backups of your project files.',
  'help.faqBetterResultsQuestion': 'How can I get better generation results?',
  'help.faqBetterResultsAnswer': 'Be specific in your shot descriptions, use reference images in Character Lab, provide clear prompts, and use the feedback system to guide regenerations. Experiment with different providers for varying styles.',
  'help.faqFailQuestion': 'What if generation fails?',
  'help.faqFailAnswer': 'Failed generations can be retried from the queue. Check the error message for details. Common issues include API limits, network problems, or content policy violations.',
